OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,FAs we recce the site, we hear
OL,7,Ffootsteps. They get louder and closer.
OL,8,FThe anticipation releases a burst of
OL,9,Fadrenalin - and it is somewhat nerve-
OL,10,Fracking at the same time.
OL,12,FWill he be with other gang members?
OL,13,FWill he be tooled up? Will he take
OL,14,Foffence to my line of questioning?
OL,16,FHe appears from the shadows of an
OL,17,Farchway. It's the first time we've met
OL,18,Fin person, but through intermediaries
OL,19,Fwe've had indirect contact for several
OL,20,Fmonths.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/13
