PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F428A1720143661
OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,F"It's hard coz they're your mates," he
OL,7,Fexplains. "They're people you love and
OL,8,Fcare about. People you'd go to war
OL,9,Ffor. People who become like family.
OL,10,FAnd trying to tell them that (you're
OL,11,Fleaving) ... well, it's hard."
OL,13,FHe describes how a lack of
OL,14,Fopportunities led to him dealing drugs.
OL,16,F"We don't get no help," he adds.
OL,17,F"We're just left to do whatever. If
OL,18,Fsomeone comes over and says 'do you
OL,19,Fwanna make a bit of money? Just sell
OL,20,Fthat'. If I'm not selling it, someone
OL,21,Felse will do it."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/13
