OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,FWith the dealing of drugs, also came
OL,7,Fthe threat of "opps" or rivals and
OL,8,Fthat inherently was dangerous for him.
OL,10,FJay explains: "If they come in our
OL,11,Fsection, then we gotta do what we
OL,12,Fgotta do. We're gonna get them. Chase
OL,13,Fthem down and let them know they can't
OL,14,Fcome in our area... through fists, and
OL,15,Fif they're carrying, we'd be carrying
OL,16,Fas well."
OL,18,F"Did you carry a knife?" I ask.
OL,19,F"Yeah," he answers.
OL,21,F"Have you ever used it?"
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/13
