OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,FHe continues: "Well, yeah, 100 per
OL,7,Fcent like, leaving the house... when
OL,8,Fyou're with your mates you're alright
OL,9,Fand that, but there could be a time
OL,10,Fwhere you're not with your boys and
OL,11,Fthen you get caught sleeping.
OL,13,F"Obviously if you do get caught
OL,14,Fsleeping, then I've got my boys and
OL,15,Fwe'll get them back."
OL,17,FI started looking into gangs in
OL,18,FNewcastle a year ago after Northumbria
OL,19,FPolice admitted for the first time
OL,20,Fthat there was an issue in the city.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G10/13
