OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,FAs my investigation unfolded, it
OL,7,Fappeared there was a correlation
OL,8,Facross the country between gangs of
OL,9,Fyouths and drill music - a form of rap
OL,10,Fthat was recently described by a judge
OL,11,Fin Newcastle as "pernicious", because
OL,12,Fit "tends to glorify violence".
OL,14,FI move the conversation with "Jay"
OL,15,Fonto this genre of music.
OL,17,FHe says: "Music's obviously like a way
OL,18,Fout, innit. To get off the streets.
OL,19,FYou rap what you're going through.
OL,20,FIt's just our life."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G11/13
