OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,FI ask him if it is acceptable to
OL,7,Fglorify violent acts within the drill
OL,8,Fmusic lyrics, posing to him that it
OL,9,Fcan appear intimidating to members of
OL,10,Fthe public too, seeing gangs in
OL,11,Fbalaclavas and carrying knives.
OL,13,FHe responds: "You know, everyone's
OL,14,Falways saying something bad about
OL,15,Fdrill music and rapping about this,
OL,16,Fbut that's my reality.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G12/13
