OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F428A1720143661
OL,3,CAn encounter with a former gang member
OL,4,Cwho has 'seen people get stabbed'
OL,6,F"That's what we see. That's what we
OL,7,Fhave to go through, y'kna? The normal
OL,8,Fperson doesn't have to watch their
OL,9,Fback, so we're only talking about what
OL,10,Fwe go through, so we can find a way
OL,11,Fout as well."
OL,13,FAnd with that, our interview is over.
OL,15,FHe walks back into the city he once
OL,16,Fdealt drugs in - a city he once
OL,17,Fcarried a knife in - a city where,
OL,18,Feven now he's 'out', he still has to
OL,19,Flook over his shoulder in.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G13/13
